---
title: Sicilian Eggplant Stew with Herbed Pork and Garlicky Ciabatta
description: Caponata is an eggplant-based dish hailing from Sicily, an island off the southern coast of Italy. It’s traditionally served as a salad, side dish, or relish, but we made it into a hearty stew with the addition of herb-infused ground pork and garlic-rubbed ciabatta.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/uk-herbed-pork-1662dff3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/uk-herbed-pork-21a7107f.pdf
course: main course
servings: 2
